column1: #Text=is an area and municipality in Melbourne , just south-east of the City Center .
#Text=It includes the main centres of South Yarra , Prahran and Toorak .
#Text=The area is regarded among Melburnians as one of the most desirable and expensive places to live .
#Text=It is very popular for its high-end shopping and exquisite dining , especially along Toorak Road in South Yarra , and Chapel Street in Prahran .
#Text=Stonnington lies just south-east of the City Center and can be easily reached by car , tram and suburban train .
#Text=Tram 8 runs along Swanston Street in the City Center to South Yarra and Toorak along Domain Road and then Toorak Road , terminating at the junction of Toorak and Glenferrie Roads .
#Text=From the City Center , South Yarra is about 15 to 20 minutes away .
#Text=Prahran is best reached from the City Center by Tram 6 ( towards Glen Iris ) .
#Text=. is served by three suburban train lines - Pakenham , Frankston and Sandringham .
#Text=South Yarra station is on Toorak Road .
#Text=. is on the Pakenham and Frankston lines and is located along Malvern Road in the southern part of the suburb .
#Text=( is located just off High St. ) . is on the Sandringham line
#Text=The main thoroughfare in South Yarra and Toorak is Toorak Road .
#Text=Chapel Street forms a major thoroughfare between South Yarra and Prahran .
#Text=The best access from the City Center is via St Kilda Road , turning left at Toorak Rd , Commercial Rd or High St.

#Text=The Chapel Street shopping district in Prahran is often called the ' longest catwalk in the Southern Hemisphere ' .
#Text=It begins in Windsor in the south and runs to the Toorak Road intersection .
#Text=The shopping strip is full of hundreds of local designer boutiques , big name fashion stores and denim specialists .
#Text=Vintage and second hand clothing stores are found towards the Windsor end of the street .
#Text=It 's also a great place to experience Melbourne 's world-renowned café culture .
#Text=Greville Street is a must-visit , lined with quirky boutiques and eateries .
#Text=Toorak Road runs through the centre of South Yarra through to Toorak .
#Text=Like Chapel Street , it is filled to the brim with brand-name stores and local boutiques .
#Text=With designs ranging from ultra feminine to almost theatrical , Alannah Hill clothes still have mainstream appeal due to great cuts and good use of fabrics .
#Text=Retro reigns supreme at this undercover market where stallholders sell off their trinkets and treasures .
#Text=Designer threads for the well-heeled missers and misters .
#Text=Music lovers haven for specialised titles , tickets for concerts and great advice on the next big thing in music .

#Text=Locals love it and shop for fresh veggies , organic food , fish and delicatessen .
#Text=The biggest shopping centre in the Southern Hemisphere .
#Text=Ranges from low-high end fashion , includes 2 food courts and countless other shops .
#Text=Another trendy place to shop , set in a historic building with an interesting history .
#Text=Along with clothes and food , there is also a cinema complex .
#Text=It is an amazing restaurant serving the best seafood in Melbourne .
#Text=It is located next to the Botanical Gardens and offeres excellent service and an amazing wine list .
#Text=Although hard to find , Hoo Haa makes up for it by showcasing a whimsical and eclectic decor that caters favorably to its clientele of swish and swank 20 and 30 somethings .
#Text=One of the most highly awarded restaurants in Australia , France Soir , as its name suggests , serves food that is as French as it gets .
#Text=Owner and sommelier Jean-Paul Prunetti has more than 1500 different European and Australian wines on offer .

#Text=Chapel Street and Toorak Road has some of the best nightlife in Australia , with most clubs open 24 hours !
#Text=Enjoy the finest fizz in this opulent but laidback setting that has a glamorous feel .
#Text=Great spot for after work drinks or a tipple on the weekend .
#Text=Has an all weather courtyard that is enjoyable throughout all seasons .
#Text=Award winning gourmet pizzas and cocktails with a modern Italian cuisine .
#Text=Borsch , Vodka and Tears is a Polish vodka bar , serving quite a number of genuine Polish vodkas , a number of other vodkas and a reasonable amount of decidedly non-Polish absinthe .
#Text=Ordering vodka in the slightly smaller tasting glasses is a comparatively economical way to drink .
#Text=With a hip , almost too cool for school clientele , BlueBar draws in its punters with a relaxed , chilled out vibe and a consisently busy crowd .
#Text=The newest bar on the Chapel St block , Electric Ladyland has found its niche with a luxurious décor and an impressive selection of cocktails .
